                  <summary>Remains of a customs pass for wine exportation.</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">4 lines of text.</note>
                     <note type="general">This text belongs to a group of 12 such customs documents discovered at Berenike.</note>
                     <note type="general">All of the orders in this group originated from one Herak- (the editors thought it best not to resolve the name) who commanded a certain Drakon to release goods for export.</note>
                     <note type="general">The word "koud( )" has been interpreted as an abbreviation for an uncertain Latin title beginning "Quad( )".</note>
